Package: curlimpersonate
Title: Use 'curl-impersonate' as the Backend for 'curl', 'httr', and 'httr2'
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Noam", "Ross", , "noam@raft.foundation", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Makes R HTTP requests carry a real browser's TLS (JA3/JA4) and
    HTTP/2 fingerprint by installing a build of the 'curl' package linked
    against 'libcurl-impersonate'. Downloads prebuilt 'libcurl-impersonate'
    binaries into a user cache (or uses a local install via the
    'CURLIMPERSONATE_HOME' environment variable), rebuilds the 'curl' package
    into a private library, and provides helpers to activate that library and
    switch the impersonation profile per session. Because 'curl', 'httr', and
    'httr2' all route through the 'curl' package, the swap applies to
    everything downstream.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Imports:
    jsonlite,
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    curl,
    httr2,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
SystemRequirements: pkg-config and a C toolchain (used to rebuild the 'curl'
    package against libcurl-impersonate)
URL: https://github.com/noamross/curlimpersonate
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
